WEBVTT

00:51.491 --> 00:53.406
Three, two, one.

00:54.320 --> 00:55.973
And...

00:55.973 --> 00:56.800
We're live.

00:59.803 --> 01:00.935
How you doin', Victor?

01:00.935 --> 01:01.762
I'm doing great.

01:01.762 --> 01:03.242
Thanks for askin'.

01:03.242 --> 01:05.113
Okay, so just for the
audience not familiar with you,

01:05.113 --> 01:06.549
briefly introduce yourself,

01:06.549 --> 01:10.684
and what you did for the
infamous Vance Institute.

01:10.684 --> 01:11.989
I was an ex-con

01:12.903 --> 01:14.514
who got a second chance at life

01:14.514 --> 01:18.431
when I came across one of
Tobin Vance's self-help books.

01:18.431 --> 01:20.172
And when I was done doing my time,

01:20.172 --> 01:22.565
I became a nurse and nutritionist,

01:22.565 --> 01:24.654
and started working at the institute.

01:24.654 --> 01:26.047
Now, that's interesting.

01:26.047 --> 01:30.051
You still credit Tobin
Vance for saving your life,

01:30.051 --> 01:32.706
even after all the things
he's been accused of?

01:32.706 --> 01:37.102
You can't discount
his earlier accomplishments

01:37.102 --> 01:39.539
just because things went south
later on.

01:43.369 --> 01:44.239
Results.

01:45.719 --> 01:46.763
That's what I'm talking about.

01:46.763 --> 01:48.417
In fact, that's all I preach.

01:49.375 --> 01:51.377
If I told you I could
save your dying child,

01:51.377 --> 01:52.552
would you care how I did it?

01:52.552 --> 01:54.119
No!

01:54.119 --> 01:58.210
You'd only be concerned with the results.

01:58.210 --> 02:02.127
If I told you I could erase
all your fears, insecurities,

02:02.127 --> 02:03.998
and personal issues,

02:03.998 --> 02:06.261
would ya care how I did it?

02:06.261 --> 02:07.132
No.

02:08.089 --> 02:10.091
You'd only be concerned about
one thing.

02:11.048 --> 02:12.615
The results.

02:12.615 --> 02:15.314
Him, what's his file say?

02:15.314 --> 02:16.837
That's Daniel White.

02:16.837 --> 02:19.709
His parents died in a
fire when he was a child.

02:19.709 --> 02:22.364
Has suicidal thoughts and tendencies.

02:22.364 --> 02:23.583
Alcoholic.

02:23.583 --> 02:26.412
Completed all of the Vance
online courses.

02:26.412 --> 02:27.543
Put him on the list.

02:28.457 --> 02:29.632
No.

02:29.632 --> 02:32.113
Suicidal tendencies are too unpredictable.

02:32.113 --> 02:34.420
Tobin says, "They make the
best members if they pass,

02:34.420 --> 02:36.248
and if they don't, they
got what they wanted".

02:36.248 --> 02:37.597
Win/win.

02:37.597 --> 02:39.207
Need I remind you

02:39.207 --> 02:41.949
that you're only supposed to
play your part and shadow me?

02:41.949 --> 02:43.298
They missed the big picture.

02:43.298 --> 02:44.125
It's almost like looking at

02:44.125 --> 02:45.170
the cracks of the statue,

02:45.170 --> 02:46.867
instead of the art itself.
- Hmm.

02:46.867 --> 02:48.869
Okay, put him on the list.

02:50.262 --> 02:51.698
But if anything happens,

02:53.352 --> 02:55.832
you have to repeat that
statement to Tobin.

02:55.832 --> 02:56.703
Copy that.

02:59.009 --> 03:00.620
So you need to ask yourself,

03:02.404 --> 03:05.668
what would it mean to you
to get everything you want

03:05.668 --> 03:06.626
in this world?

03:08.715 --> 03:10.717
And that answer,

03:10.717 --> 03:13.154
it better be amazing.

03:15.722 --> 03:17.550
Let's back it up, okay?

03:17.550 --> 03:20.683
Tobin Vance, for the past 20 years,

03:20.683 --> 03:25.471
has been one of the leading
self-help gurus in...

03:25.471 --> 03:26.907
The US?

03:26.907 --> 03:29.431
- In the world.
- The world.

03:29.431 --> 03:33.522
Over 20,000 people
signed up for his course,

03:33.522 --> 03:38.223
and he has ardent, dedicated
followers, like yourself?

03:38.223 --> 03:39.049
That's right.

03:39.049 --> 03:40.964
It all came

03:40.964 --> 03:44.141
crashing down!

03:44.141 --> 03:48.537
Racketeering, sexual
abuse, money laundering.

03:48.537 --> 03:49.930
Many of the victims,

03:49.930 --> 03:53.150
or survivors, as they
prefer to be referred to,

03:53.150 --> 03:55.327
say that they were manipulated,

03:55.327 --> 03:59.026
that what started out as a
self-help

03:59.026 --> 04:00.245
and leadership seminar

04:01.202 --> 04:02.986
became a cult.

04:04.684 --> 04:06.207
Hello.

04:06.207 --> 04:08.122
I am Dr. Elizabeth White,

04:09.166 --> 04:11.473
and I'm here to say, congratulations.

04:12.779 --> 04:13.954
You've all been chosen.

04:16.261 --> 04:17.131
For what?

04:18.001 --> 04:21.440
The Vance Institute Advanced
Treatment Program, John.

04:22.876 --> 04:24.486
This is a five day retreat,

04:24.486 --> 04:28.011
where you will be guaranteed results.

04:28.011 --> 04:30.231
You all have contracts,

04:30.231 --> 04:32.189
and I'd like you to review the details.

04:32.189 --> 04:33.930
So this is some kind of

04:35.541 --> 04:37.194
advanced training?

04:37.194 --> 04:38.457
Mm-hmm.

04:38.457 --> 04:39.327
It's happening.

04:39.327 --> 04:40.676
It's actually happening!

04:40.676 --> 04:41.808
Yes, Frank.

04:43.026 --> 04:45.246
And you are all followers of
Tobin Vance

04:45.246 --> 04:47.770
and the Vance Institute Training Program,

04:47.770 --> 04:49.903
and we feel that you have the potential

04:49.903 --> 04:52.384
to be active contributing members.

04:52.384 --> 04:53.994
You filled
out a form

04:53.994 --> 04:55.038
when you came here today,

04:55.038 --> 04:57.302
and we feel we can help you.

04:58.477 --> 04:59.913
How?

04:59.913 --> 05:01.697
You are all invited

05:01.697 --> 05:06.311
to the Vance Institute Advanced
Treatment Retreat Center

05:06.311 --> 05:07.442
in Kirkcaldy, Scotland.

05:07.442 --> 05:08.704
Wow!

05:08.704 --> 05:10.706
It's definitely something to
say wow to.

05:10.706 --> 05:13.230
But we are also hoping
that you'll say yes to it.

05:13.230 --> 05:14.319
Please review the contracts.

05:14.319 --> 05:15.755
We want to make sure that you are

05:15.755 --> 05:18.105
freely entering into
this agreement with us.

05:20.673 --> 05:21.500
Yes, John?

05:23.371 --> 05:26.592
It says this is $75,000.

05:28.898 --> 05:33.642
Yes, but here's the good news.

05:33.642 --> 05:34.904
That fee is waived.

05:35.992 --> 05:39.126
You'll only be charged that
amount if you decide to quit.

05:39.126 --> 05:41.041
I don't know if I'm
ready for this program.

05:41.041 --> 05:42.521
You're not sure?

05:42.521 --> 05:45.306
A five day retreat in
the middle of the woods?

05:45.306 --> 05:46.394
I mean, I just don't know

05:46.394 --> 05:47.308
if I'm ready.
- Are you not ready

05:47.308 --> 05:48.265
to get over your problems, John?

05:48.265 --> 05:49.832
I mean, I'd love that.

05:49.832 --> 05:50.659
I'd love that.

05:50.659 --> 05:51.530
But-
- But...

05:52.444 --> 05:54.750
But is the killer word, John.

05:56.273 --> 05:58.711
I'm inclined to agree with you, John.

06:00.974 --> 06:02.454
You're not ready.

06:02.454 --> 06:06.109
That means Tobin does not
want you in the program.

06:07.459 --> 06:08.285
Wait.

06:09.156 --> 06:10.418
Would-
- Good luck, John,

06:10.418 --> 06:13.595
with your life, and your issues.

06:13.595 --> 06:14.466
Fuck!

06:16.468 --> 06:17.599
Well...

06:22.735 --> 06:23.736
The door is there.

06:30.090 --> 06:32.179
Anyone else?

06:32.179 --> 06:33.528
Great!

06:33.528 --> 06:36.401
Now we have a group ready for change.

07:00.642 --> 07:01.861
Welcome.

07:01.861 --> 07:03.819
Welcome, welcome.

07:03.819 --> 07:05.691
I hope you're all as excited to
be here

07:05.691 --> 07:06.996
as we are to have you?

07:08.128 --> 07:10.130
Please, please, form a
half-circle around the fire

07:10.130 --> 07:11.305
and we can get started.

07:12.654 --> 07:14.482
It's freezing.

07:14.482 --> 07:16.484
That's not an accident, Lily.

07:16.484 --> 07:21.184
It's freezing because life
is cold, harsh, unforgiving.

07:21.184 --> 07:22.534
Comfort!

07:22.534 --> 07:24.666
Comfort breeds weak mammals,

07:24.666 --> 07:26.494
and we're all mammals, are we
not?

07:27.669 --> 07:30.280
Struggles in life could make us stronger

07:30.280 --> 07:31.760
or they could crush us,

07:31.760 --> 07:32.761
but not us,

07:32.761 --> 07:35.677
because we are about to evolve.

07:35.677 --> 07:38.985
We're about to shed the husk of
the weak,

07:38.985 --> 07:41.466
the impulsive, the
mournful, the deceitful.

07:41.466 --> 07:43.032
Say yes to this!

07:43.032 --> 07:43.903
Yes.

07:44.773 --> 07:47.254
Now, before you were invited here,

07:47.254 --> 07:48.516
you were given a request

07:48.516 --> 07:50.562
to bring an item of extreme importance.

07:50.562 --> 07:53.434
Now, this personal object
should have significant meaning.

07:53.434 --> 07:55.784
It should be a representation

07:55.784 --> 07:59.048
of the life that you want to
leave behind.

07:59.048 --> 08:01.355
If you'll all pull out
these objects, please?

08:05.968 --> 08:08.449
When a lobster gets too big for
its shell,

08:08.449 --> 08:09.494
it breaks free,

08:10.495 --> 08:11.408
and then it's weak.

08:11.408 --> 08:13.193
It's vulnerable, it's raw,

08:13.193 --> 08:16.544
and it needs to build a
thicker, stronger shell.

08:16.544 --> 08:18.285
We, here, now!

08:18.285 --> 08:21.506
We are shedding our shells.

08:21.506 --> 08:24.291
Now, we'll go around one by one,

08:24.291 --> 08:27.642
and you can explain your
object and its significance.

08:29.470 --> 08:30.297
Jesse.

08:32.908 --> 08:35.607
My parents sent me
off to boarding school,

08:35.607 --> 08:37.913
but I didn't quite fit in with
the others.

08:39.524 --> 08:42.309
The headmaster noticed that
I had an eye for detail,

08:43.484 --> 08:45.181
and said I might enjoy reading about

08:45.181 --> 08:47.575
the greatest detective there
ever was.

08:49.098 --> 08:51.797
To this day, never been without
a copy.

08:52.798 --> 08:55.452
Sometimes people focus
too much on the details

08:55.452 --> 08:56.845
and they miss the big picture.

08:56.845 --> 08:58.455
It's almost like looking
at the cracks in a statue,

08:58.455 --> 08:59.761
instead of the art itself.

09:01.328 --> 09:02.155
Nicole.

09:03.852 --> 09:07.682
My father gave me this
doll for my birthday

09:09.858 --> 09:11.599
the year before my mother shot him.

09:13.688 --> 09:16.343
It was all I had left of who he was

09:16.343 --> 09:17.649
- before he-
- Before

09:18.650 --> 09:19.868
your mother went to jail

09:19.868 --> 09:21.957
and you became ward of
the state at 13, right?

09:23.219 --> 09:24.873
Right.

09:24.873 --> 09:28.616
So that doll represents
someone who is never really there.

09:28.616 --> 09:30.618
These people were predators,

09:30.618 --> 09:32.881
and you defended the
sheep's cloak they wore.

09:34.840 --> 09:35.710
Lily.

09:40.410 --> 09:41.498
When I was little,

09:42.804 --> 09:45.154
our house was filled
with photos of my mother.

09:46.025 --> 09:47.809
I look at this photo,

09:47.809 --> 09:49.768
think that my mom was a princess.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.249
She died of cancer when I was 14.

09:56.165 --> 09:59.386
Your mother was Feria Lee?

09:59.386 --> 10:00.692
Yes.

10:00.692 --> 10:04.391
Okay, from 1980, she started modeling,

10:04.391 --> 10:07.046
and did her last runway in 1986.

10:07.046 --> 10:11.224
Then from '86 to '92, she
raised you, wrote two books,

10:11.224 --> 10:12.747
trained show dogs,

10:12.747 --> 10:14.836
and increased funding and
research for breast cancer,

10:14.836 --> 10:17.360
and yet, the image you hold onto

10:17.360 --> 10:19.449
is something that existed for
six years.

10:20.799 --> 10:23.366
If I asked your mother what her
greatest accomplishment was,

10:23.366 --> 10:25.325
do you think she'd say
her modeling career?

10:26.935 --> 10:28.284
Frank.

10:30.286 --> 10:33.202
This is a game token
from Time Warp Arcade.

10:34.290 --> 10:35.117
Go on.

10:35.988 --> 10:37.511
Was.

10:37.511 --> 10:40.340
It's an arcade token I've kept
with me since I was a kid.

10:40.340 --> 10:42.429
You liked arcade games?

10:42.429 --> 10:43.691
I was obsessed, yeah.

10:45.693 --> 10:48.261
You told us you lost your
brother in a car accident

10:48.261 --> 10:49.697
when you were 11, right?

10:49.697 --> 10:51.307
Yeah.

10:51.307 --> 10:55.094
And where were you going when
the car got in the accident?

10:56.922 --> 10:58.053
Time Warp Arcade.

11:00.099 --> 11:01.361
Who was driving?

11:04.233 --> 11:05.060
My dad.

11:06.540 --> 11:08.107
You get along with your
father?

11:09.848 --> 11:10.675
He hates me.

11:11.850 --> 11:13.765
After that day, did he hit you
ever?

11:16.768 --> 11:17.594
All the time.

11:18.987 --> 11:20.032
Hmm.

11:20.032 --> 11:21.903
You think you deserved it?

11:21.903 --> 11:22.774
Well, I did, yeah.

11:25.385 --> 11:27.430
I was the shit brother.

11:27.430 --> 11:29.171
Frank, look at me!

11:29.171 --> 11:31.434
Your father was driving.

11:31.434 --> 11:32.827
You blame yourself.

11:32.827 --> 11:35.177
You play that victim card.

11:35.177 --> 11:37.745
But your father was too weak of
a person

11:37.745 --> 11:39.138
to admit that it was his fault,

11:39.138 --> 11:40.487
and he blamed you,

11:40.487 --> 11:42.054
so you carry the weight of that blame.

11:42.054 --> 11:43.882
You carry the weight of that token,

11:43.882 --> 11:45.448
and it's weighing you down.

11:45.448 --> 11:49.714
You haven't even begun to become
the man that you could be.

11:51.019 --> 11:51.846
Daniel.

11:56.938 --> 11:58.592
I see where this is going.

11:59.898 --> 12:00.725
Okay.

12:04.250 --> 12:05.730
This was my dad's...

12:09.124 --> 12:11.213
My dad's favorite bourbon.

12:11.213 --> 12:12.737
And what happened to your
father?

12:13.912 --> 12:15.565
You know all about us.

12:15.565 --> 12:17.045
That seems-
- What happened?

12:19.744 --> 12:21.093
He committed suicide.

12:23.617 --> 12:24.444
You miss him?

12:25.575 --> 12:26.446
Every day.

12:27.664 --> 12:29.971
He blamed you for ruining
his life, didn't he?

12:32.147 --> 12:32.974
Yeah.

12:34.019 --> 12:37.500
Your father placed an
enormous burden on you to carry.

12:37.500 --> 12:39.154
You drink to feel numb.

12:40.460 --> 12:43.680
Folks, I want you all to
destroy these objects.

12:43.680 --> 12:45.421
Place them right in the fire,

12:45.421 --> 12:47.597
because these objects are
holding us back

12:47.597 --> 12:52.254
from becoming the people
that we were meant to be.

12:56.824 --> 12:58.434
Fuck it!

13:13.101 --> 13:13.972
Hand it to me, Daniel.

13:13.972 --> 13:14.842
I'll throw it in for you.

13:14.842 --> 13:16.539
Don't, Frank!

13:16.539 --> 13:18.193
That's Daniel's past to discard.

13:20.892 --> 13:22.545
He doesn't look so good.

13:22.545 --> 13:25.287
Frank has
his own demons to face.

13:25.287 --> 13:26.898
You're all free to throw on a blanket,

13:26.898 --> 13:29.683
and Elizabeth will lead you
back to the retreat house.

13:40.825 --> 13:41.913
What's wrong, Daniel?

13:44.002 --> 13:44.872
Don't like fire.

13:45.830 --> 13:46.831
Daniel, look at me.

13:49.224 --> 13:50.051
Look at me!

13:51.487 --> 13:53.402
You could stay where you are.

13:53.402 --> 13:54.751
You can live in the past,

13:54.751 --> 13:56.884
or you could face your fears,

13:56.884 --> 13:59.278
and become the person
that you were meant to be.

14:02.498 --> 14:04.109
I can't.

14:07.808 --> 14:10.115
The retreat is about a
quarter mile from here.

14:10.115 --> 14:11.681
You can walk there yourself,

14:11.681 --> 14:13.770
and one of my associates will
get your

14:13.770 --> 14:16.382
fucking worthless ass off my property,

14:16.382 --> 14:18.253
you weak fuck!

14:18.253 --> 14:19.907
And then we'll send you the bill.

15:26.278 --> 15:27.496
Your phones.

15:28.410 --> 15:31.196
Having no contact with the
outside world

15:31.196 --> 15:33.198
will be essential for your growth.

15:35.504 --> 15:38.246
You'll be returned your phones
by the end of the retreat.

15:40.466 --> 15:41.380
Yes, Jesse?

15:42.207 --> 15:43.425
What's with the rooms?

15:45.036 --> 15:46.559
I'm not sure what that means?

15:48.039 --> 15:51.172
The walls in the rooms,
they're reinforced.

15:52.260 --> 15:54.306
You're planning to lock us in?

15:54.306 --> 15:56.656
God, no!

15:57.570 --> 15:58.963
You can try the locks yourselves.

15:58.963 --> 16:01.226
There's no way to lock
them from the outside.

16:02.140 --> 16:04.664
But they are soundproof.

16:05.839 --> 16:07.319
Why is that?

16:07.319 --> 16:08.624
In the past,

16:08.624 --> 16:10.757
different people have
reacted in varying ways

16:10.757 --> 16:11.627
to the treatment.

16:12.889 --> 16:15.196
Some yell and scream,

16:15.196 --> 16:17.720
some laugh, some talk to themselves.

16:17.720 --> 16:20.419
Either way, that is your own journey,

16:20.419 --> 16:22.334
and not one to be heard by the others.

16:25.685 --> 16:27.295
So when does all this start?

16:28.253 --> 16:29.994
First thing in the morning.

16:31.604 --> 16:35.695
And now, I have good news,

16:35.695 --> 16:37.044
and then, even better news.

16:45.574 --> 16:46.967
Each day, you will be required

16:46.967 --> 16:50.927
to take these mental
enhancers and vitamins.

16:50.927 --> 16:54.279
They will help you to truly
feel the effects of the changes

16:54.279 --> 16:56.063
you're so ready to make.

16:59.110 --> 17:01.503
You need to trust us, if you
want results.

17:04.419 --> 17:05.725
What's the bad news?

17:07.553 --> 17:10.773
Yeah, you said there
was even more good news?

17:10.773 --> 17:12.906
Oh, [laughs] yes.

17:14.777 --> 17:17.954
Tonight, you get to have fun.

17:17.954 --> 17:21.045
Introduce yourselves, share stories.

17:21.045 --> 17:23.308
I want you to truly
get to know each other.

17:25.049 --> 17:27.442
Tomorrow, your new life begins.

17:28.574 --> 17:30.793
Hey, where's Daniel?

17:37.931 --> 17:39.237
He wanted to be with his family

17:39.237 --> 17:42.283
more than he wanted to
grow into a new human.

17:42.283 --> 17:43.154
But don't worry.

17:44.981 --> 17:46.592
Those who fail

17:46.592 --> 17:49.029
end up paying for those
whose fees we've waived.

18:04.131 --> 18:05.393
My name is Nicole,

18:05.393 --> 18:08.353
and I'm here to get over some insecurities

18:08.353 --> 18:11.617
and trust issues I've had
stemming from my younger years.

18:12.966 --> 18:14.315
My name is Frank,

18:14.315 --> 18:17.971
and I'm here because I
can't stand up for myself.

18:19.103 --> 18:21.409
I'm Lily, and I'd like to

18:21.409 --> 18:23.890
work on a eating disorder that
I've had.

18:24.804 --> 18:26.066
Jesus Christ!

18:26.762 --> 18:27.546
What?

18:27.546 --> 18:28.808
My name's Jesse,

18:28.808 --> 18:30.375
and unlike you three,

18:30.375 --> 18:32.159
I'll actually have the balls
to tell you my real problem.

18:32.159 --> 18:33.508
Hey!

18:33.508 --> 18:34.422
None of you would've come here

18:34.422 --> 18:36.163
if you had these minor issues.

18:40.776 --> 18:42.169
Trust issues?

18:42.169 --> 18:43.562
Go see a shrink.

18:43.562 --> 18:45.825
And you, buy a book on personal power.

18:47.174 --> 18:48.349
Hang on.

18:48.349 --> 18:50.525
Don't assume you know anything
about us.

18:50.525 --> 18:51.439
That's just it.

18:52.440 --> 18:54.181
We're supposed to get to know
each other.

18:54.181 --> 18:55.226
Truly get to know each other.

18:55.226 --> 18:56.836
That's what Elizabeth said.

18:58.229 --> 19:01.884
So Nicole, wanna tell us
why you're really here?

19:06.498 --> 19:08.500
I was raped by my father.

19:13.200 --> 19:14.070
I...

19:15.071 --> 19:15.855
I didn't...

19:15.855 --> 19:17.378
I'm sorry.

19:17.378 --> 19:20.425
There was a time where I
couldn't even say that out loud.

19:22.296 --> 19:24.037
But as much as you seem
like an asshole, Jesse,

19:24.037 --> 19:25.256
you're absolutely right,

19:26.387 --> 19:27.519
I'm here to change.

19:30.478 --> 19:32.263
And Elizabeth told us
to share our stories.

19:32.263 --> 19:33.177
So...

19:34.439 --> 19:35.353
What's your story?

19:42.838 --> 19:45.972
I'm here for anxiety and depression.

19:47.669 --> 19:49.018
It may not sound like much,

19:50.324 --> 19:52.935
but

19:52.935 --> 19:55.199
sometimes I can't leave
the house because of it.

19:56.374 --> 19:58.463
I get in a funk, and I
can't get over of it.

19:59.681 --> 20:02.815
My eating disorder is bigger
than just a normal issue.

20:04.904 --> 20:06.688
I can't stop myself.

20:10.301 --> 20:12.520
Well, I've been bullied my
whole life.

20:13.565 --> 20:14.957
When I was 12,

20:14.957 --> 20:17.177
a bully beat me up in
front of the entire school,

20:18.439 --> 20:20.267
and I peed my pants when it happened.

20:22.138 --> 20:24.532
After that, I was known
as Frank the Urinator

20:24.532 --> 20:26.273
for the rest of school.

20:30.930 --> 20:32.714
Go ahead and laugh, guys.

20:32.714 --> 20:33.889
I mean, we are meant to be

20:33.889 --> 20:35.674
gettin' to know each other,
after all.

20:35.674 --> 20:37.502
And besides,

20:37.502 --> 20:39.634
I think this booze is startin'
to kick in.

21:16.410 --> 21:19.326
- Everybody okay?

21:20.458 --> 21:22.808
- What the hell is that?

21:22.808 --> 21:25.898
I'm assuming it's a sign to
tell us it's time to go to bed.

21:25.898 --> 21:28.030
No.

21:33.993 --> 21:36.517
Alcohol.

21:36.517 --> 21:39.041
Is this alcohol affecting you?

21:39.041 --> 21:41.740
Yeah.

21:42.741 --> 21:44.395
Am I dreaming this?

22:58.382 --> 23:00.601
Day one, the
followers were given

23:00.601 --> 23:03.430
some kind of drunk cocktail,

23:03.430 --> 23:05.301
which appeared to knock them out.

23:06.868 --> 23:09.436
It was potentially causing hallucinations.

26:11.357 --> 26:13.141
How did you know she'd kill him,

26:14.055 --> 26:15.491
and not the other way around?

26:16.797 --> 26:17.668
We didn't.

26:18.756 --> 26:19.931
So where is Tobin?

26:19.931 --> 26:21.236
Where is he?

26:21.236 --> 26:22.281
Come on, man.

26:22.281 --> 26:24.152
I don't know where he's at.

26:24.152 --> 26:25.763
Oh, come on, man!

26:25.763 --> 26:27.329
Stop bullshitting me.

26:27.329 --> 26:28.504
You know where he is.

26:28.504 --> 26:29.723
Come on, admit it.

26:29.723 --> 26:31.507
He's still running the Vance Institutes.

26:31.507 --> 26:32.726
He's still running this shit,
but from...

26:32.726 --> 26:33.640
He's hiding.

26:33.640 --> 26:34.467
He's in hiding.

26:34.467 --> 26:35.294
But where?

26:36.208 --> 26:38.123
There's reports he's in the UK.

26:38.123 --> 26:39.733
Yeah, in the UK,

26:39.733 --> 26:42.170
And he's still selling this
bullshit as wellness retreats.

26:43.171 --> 26:44.651
That's the reports.

26:44.651 --> 26:46.435
I don't know shit, man.

27:29.391 --> 27:30.871
Good mornin'.

27:31.916 --> 27:33.004
Sleep well?

27:34.527 --> 27:35.833
Yeah.

27:35.833 --> 27:36.921
You?

27:36.921 --> 27:38.400
I passed out.

27:38.400 --> 27:39.401
I did, too.

27:39.401 --> 27:40.707
I know, Frank.

27:40.707 --> 27:42.491
I dragged you to your room.

27:42.491 --> 27:43.928
You seem fine, Jesse?

27:43.928 --> 27:46.017
Yeah, I was hiding it well.

27:46.974 --> 27:50.325
Well, if no one's gonna
come out and say it, I will.

27:51.762 --> 27:52.632
Did they drug us?

27:53.764 --> 27:56.680
We took those pills on their orders.

27:57.637 --> 27:59.683
Maybe mixing them with alcohol
did it?

28:10.737 --> 28:11.999
Good morning.

28:14.262 --> 28:16.003
First light was a little rough, eh?

28:17.091 --> 28:19.093
Maybe you needed to let off some
steam?

28:19.964 --> 28:21.269
That's what you call it?

28:22.836 --> 28:25.839
Did y'all get a
little crazy?

28:25.839 --> 28:28.842
Maybe it was the drugs, Tobin?

28:28.842 --> 28:30.888
Oh, yes, the vitamins we gave you.

28:31.889 --> 28:34.108
Don't worry, they still did
their job.

28:35.588 --> 28:37.111
What the hell does that mean?

28:37.938 --> 28:39.026
The vitamins,

28:40.201 --> 28:42.900
they sometimes have a reaction

28:42.900 --> 28:44.597
with extreme levels of alcohol.

28:45.511 --> 28:46.599
Maybe we should have warned you?

28:46.599 --> 28:48.644
But you are all adults.

28:49.776 --> 28:51.822
I mean, Jesse here, he looks fine.

28:51.822 --> 28:56.478
Well, I've been able to
handle alcohol my whole life.

28:56.478 --> 28:58.176
My family are all big drinkers.

28:59.220 --> 29:00.047
Got it.

29:02.267 --> 29:03.355
How 'bout you, Nicole?

29:06.184 --> 29:07.315
What?

29:07.315 --> 29:12.233
I mean, did you have
hallucinations?

29:12.233 --> 29:13.060
No.

29:13.060 --> 29:14.975
No, just a head rush.

29:16.411 --> 29:19.110
You see?

29:19.110 --> 29:20.589
I mean, y'all look tired,

29:20.589 --> 29:23.679
but do any of you have the
classic hangover symptoms,

29:23.679 --> 29:25.072
headache, shaking hands?

29:25.943 --> 29:26.770
You see?

29:26.770 --> 29:28.554
The vitamins do work!

29:29.816 --> 29:31.383
Folks, we know all about you.

29:31.383 --> 29:34.038
We know your fears, your
weaknesses, your issues,

29:34.038 --> 29:36.823
your hopes, your dreams.

29:36.823 --> 29:39.739
Elizabeth here has your applications.

29:39.739 --> 29:41.219
And from now on,

29:41.219 --> 29:45.614
the rest of this retreat
will be focused on results.

29:45.614 --> 29:48.530
That's a word I love to use lately.

29:48.530 --> 29:50.968
So last night, y'all needed
to let off some steam.

29:50.968 --> 29:52.317
It's fine!

29:52.317 --> 29:55.842
But now, we have to
start with a clean slate.

29:55.842 --> 29:57.235
The question becomes,

29:57.235 --> 30:01.152
how do we clean that slate
quickly?

30:03.763 --> 30:06.853
And what, are these gonna do
this?

30:06.853 --> 30:08.507
They'll help you focus.

30:08.507 --> 30:09.725
Take them.

30:12.467 --> 30:13.642
You do what I say!

30:16.863 --> 30:18.734
Who's ready to focus?

30:18.734 --> 30:20.345
Now, how did you all feel
when I yelled that way?

30:20.345 --> 30:21.955
That was scary, right?

30:21.955 --> 30:23.565
You reacted.

30:23.565 --> 30:27.134
When you're upset, when you're
angry, depressed, any of it,

30:27.134 --> 30:28.440
that's all you can focus on.

30:28.440 --> 30:29.789
Wouldn't you agree?

30:29.789 --> 30:30.877
Let's say this.

30:30.877 --> 30:32.052
Say you're driving down the road,

30:32.052 --> 30:33.488
and you're living with those emotions.

30:33.488 --> 30:35.664
You're angry, depressed,
sad, something like that,

30:35.664 --> 30:37.492
and a deer runs out,

30:37.492 --> 30:39.886
and runs right into your car.

30:39.886 --> 30:41.148
What happens?

30:41.148 --> 30:42.671
You react.

30:42.671 --> 30:43.977
The adrenaline kicks in.

30:44.848 --> 30:45.936
Exactly.

30:45.936 --> 30:46.806
Good.

30:46.806 --> 30:47.851
Good job, both of you.

30:48.808 --> 30:50.505
Let me ask another question.

30:51.898 --> 30:54.509
When you're dealing with that situation,

30:54.509 --> 30:59.210
what happens to your
anger, your depression,

30:59.210 --> 31:00.864
and your sadness?

31:02.039 --> 31:03.301
They disappear.

31:03.301 --> 31:04.171
Bingo!

31:04.171 --> 31:05.259
Good.

31:05.259 --> 31:06.695
Nicole, good.

31:06.695 --> 31:10.395
All you can focus on in
that moment is the reaction.

31:15.400 --> 31:18.882
Have any of you heard of the
Schmidt's sting pain index?

31:20.361 --> 31:22.102
It's a measure of the amount of pain

31:22.102 --> 31:24.452
given off by an insect bite or sting.

31:25.497 --> 31:27.760
Level one is your basic bee sting,

31:27.760 --> 31:30.545
and it goes all the way up to
level five.

31:30.545 --> 31:33.853
Level five is shared by three creatures,

31:33.853 --> 31:36.812
the bullet ant, the tarantula hawk,

31:37.988 --> 31:40.381
and these little bad boys right here,

31:40.381 --> 31:42.644
the devil's tooth leech.

31:42.644 --> 31:46.561
This creature transmits
a venom into its victim.

31:46.561 --> 31:47.606
It's excruciating.

31:48.868 --> 31:50.609
It lasts for up to five hours,

31:50.609 --> 31:53.264
but then, it's over.

31:55.309 --> 31:57.877
We are growing.

32:04.014 --> 32:05.580
You were raped.

32:07.321 --> 32:10.542
You are a weak person who's
bullied at every turn.

32:11.717 --> 32:13.937
You suffer from crippling depression.

32:15.112 --> 32:17.766
And you can't say no to
anything, especially food.

32:18.854 --> 32:21.509
Folks, don't shy away from these
issues!

32:21.509 --> 32:22.858
Own them!

32:22.858 --> 32:24.382
Focus on them!

32:24.382 --> 32:25.949
Let them flood your mind.

32:25.949 --> 32:29.039
Close your eyes and do this.

32:29.039 --> 32:29.953
Now...

32:33.347 --> 32:34.958
Are you focusing on your issue?

32:37.134 --> 32:38.526
Yes.

32:38.526 --> 32:39.397
Good.

32:59.547 --> 33:01.810
Please, please, please?

33:01.810 --> 33:02.768
You do what I say!

33:02.768 --> 33:04.726
I will not ask you again!

33:19.089 --> 33:20.612
You think you scare me?

33:20.612 --> 33:21.917
You tell me.

33:21.917 --> 33:24.355
I took a bullet to the
shoulder once.

33:24.355 --> 33:25.486
Oh, yeah?

33:25.486 --> 33:26.357
Where was that?

33:35.801 --> 33:37.455
I can't.

33:37.455 --> 33:39.326
I can't.

33:39.326 --> 33:41.067
You say yes to everything else,

33:41.067 --> 33:42.808
and you're gonna say no to this?

33:42.808 --> 33:44.505
Are you crazy?

33:44.505 --> 33:45.985
What the hell lesson is this
teaching us?

33:46.899 --> 33:49.510
You obviously weren't
listening.

33:49.510 --> 33:50.903
No!

33:50.903 --> 33:52.687
No, I won't do this!

33:52.687 --> 33:54.385
No-

34:05.135 --> 34:10.096
Now, who's still thinking
about their problems?

34:22.717 --> 34:24.850
Pretty intense first day, huh?

34:24.850 --> 34:26.025
I'd say so.

34:27.418 --> 34:28.984
What the fuck was that?

34:28.984 --> 34:31.248
No way was I letting that
fuckin' thing sting me!

34:31.248 --> 34:34.381
Listen, they're just trying
it to get inside your head.

34:34.381 --> 34:36.079
Of course they're tryin'
to get inside our heads!

34:36.079 --> 34:37.645
That's the reason we're here!

34:37.645 --> 34:39.212
I'll be honest.

34:39.212 --> 34:40.344
I feel great!

34:41.910 --> 34:43.912
- What?

34:43.912 --> 34:45.914
I faced a challenge!

34:45.914 --> 34:48.352
I didn't back down!

34:48.352 --> 34:50.615
You know how long it's been
since I tried something

34:50.615 --> 34:52.356
and I was successful?

34:53.531 --> 34:55.489
You call that success?

34:56.882 --> 34:59.276
Is there any other way to
perceive it?

34:59.276 --> 35:01.191
Well, what was it for?

35:01.191 --> 35:02.496
To fuck with us.

35:07.066 --> 35:08.154
No!

35:12.637 --> 35:13.855
To clear our minds.

35:15.814 --> 35:16.684
I don't know about you,

35:16.684 --> 35:18.904
but my mind is clear.

35:23.822 --> 35:25.128
Whatever you say, man.

35:28.914 --> 35:31.656
Let's just see how tomorrow goes.

35:39.533 --> 35:41.274
You should embrace this training.

35:42.667 --> 35:44.103
Training?

35:44.103 --> 35:47.454
I'm not gonna take a fuckin'
bite from a giant leech!

35:47.454 --> 35:50.675
I'm not crazy.

36:22.489 --> 36:24.361
No!

36:42.944 --> 36:44.207
Good morning.

36:45.512 --> 36:47.949
Let's get started on day two.

36:49.299 --> 36:50.648
Shouldn't we...

36:50.648 --> 36:52.258
Shouldn't we wait for Lily?

36:53.564 --> 36:56.393
Lily is on her own path for now.

37:15.368 --> 37:16.239
Hey.

37:18.153 --> 37:19.503
Oh, hi.

37:19.503 --> 37:21.809
You're-
- The guy from the speech.

37:22.723 --> 37:25.291
Elizabeth gave me a call and
said I was back in the program.

37:27.685 --> 37:29.426
You gotta be kidding me?

37:29.426 --> 37:30.296
What?

37:32.951 --> 37:34.605
I guess I'm being kicked out.

37:35.736 --> 37:36.650
What do you mean?

37:37.608 --> 37:40.175
I failed to do the exercise yesterday,

37:40.175 --> 37:41.916
and I was punished last night,

37:41.916 --> 37:43.962
and now I'm gone.

37:43.962 --> 37:48.009
Hey, nobody told me I was
replacing anybody, okay?

37:49.315 --> 37:51.099
I mean, did somebody talk to
you?

37:52.579 --> 37:53.406
No.

37:56.409 --> 37:57.497
They just tortured me.

37:58.716 --> 38:00.805
Yesterday, Tobin challenged us
to get bit

38:00.805 --> 38:02.720
by this devil's tooth leech thing.

38:05.070 --> 38:06.289
I refused.

38:07.507 --> 38:10.510
And last night, I woke up tied
to my bed,

38:10.510 --> 38:12.033
and there were a dozen on me.

38:12.947 --> 38:13.774
Holy shit!

38:15.080 --> 38:16.299
I mean, were you bitten?

38:17.300 --> 38:19.650
So many times that I blacked out.

38:19.650 --> 38:20.520
Wow!

38:23.218 --> 38:25.917
I bet it was hard to focus on anything

38:27.701 --> 38:28.963
while that was happening?

38:31.401 --> 38:33.141
You sound just like Tobin.

38:34.839 --> 38:35.840
I do.

38:35.840 --> 38:38.321
Well, hey, okay, I'm just

38:39.278 --> 38:42.150
trying to figure out what
the lesson is in there.

38:42.150 --> 38:43.369
Whatever.

38:43.369 --> 38:45.371
I guess that's why I'm being
kicked out?

38:47.025 --> 38:47.852
Hey.

38:49.549 --> 38:50.420
You're still here.

38:52.030 --> 38:54.032
Hey, I don't see any bags packed.

38:56.426 --> 38:58.210
What's your name again?

38:58.210 --> 38:59.080
John.

39:00.081 --> 39:00.952
I'm Lily.

39:02.170 --> 39:05.043
It's nice to meet you again.

39:06.131 --> 39:07.219
You know, John,

39:09.526 --> 39:10.701
I don't know,

39:13.051 --> 39:16.271
maybe in some sick way I
needed that last night?

39:17.316 --> 39:19.797
But honestly, when those
bugs were biting me,

39:20.972 --> 39:22.321
you were right.

39:24.497 --> 39:27.195
There was nothing else
on my mind except for...

39:29.546 --> 39:30.677
Surviving.

39:31.765 --> 39:35.334
And maybe that was Tobin's
lesson?

39:37.380 --> 39:38.206
I guess.

39:39.773 --> 39:41.645
And nobody's asked you
to leave?

39:43.386 --> 39:45.126
Nobody.

39:45.126 --> 39:46.563
Then I'm sure you're still in.

39:48.478 --> 39:53.439
And you can beat this eating disorder.

39:54.135 --> 39:56.399
I never told you that's
what I was here for.

39:58.923 --> 39:59.837
I'm sorry.

39:59.837 --> 40:01.055
I was just...

40:01.055 --> 40:01.969
I was makin' a guess.

40:01.969 --> 40:04.450
I'm so fucking insensitive!

40:04.450 --> 40:05.538
So fucking [mumbles]!

40:05.538 --> 40:06.626
What the fuck is wrong with
you?!

40:06.626 --> 40:07.627
You're just so fucking
insensitive!

40:07.627 --> 40:09.063
Just lose your fuckin' shit,

40:09.063 --> 40:10.587
and you just fuckin' say
something like that?!

40:10.587 --> 40:11.675
Fuck.

40:13.241 --> 40:14.678
When you want something in life,

40:14.678 --> 40:16.419
you can't wait for it to come to you,

40:16.419 --> 40:17.898
'cause it never will.

40:17.898 --> 40:20.292
Imagine if I had a rabbit right here,

40:20.292 --> 40:23.600
what would be the first
thought that came to your mind?

40:23.600 --> 40:25.515
Don't mind if that thing bites
us?

40:25.515 --> 40:28.909
The essence
of a rabbit is to run.

40:28.909 --> 40:31.216
It runs to its next survival spot.

40:31.216 --> 40:34.480
You need to have this essence.

40:34.480 --> 40:35.438
Do you understand?

40:37.135 --> 40:38.310
I don't.

40:38.310 --> 40:40.312
That's fine.

40:40.312 --> 40:42.967
Nicole, let me make it as
simple as possible for you.

40:42.967 --> 40:46.492
What if I told you there was a
rabbit here on these grounds,

40:46.492 --> 40:48.494
and if you could find the rabbit,

40:48.494 --> 40:51.715
the rabbit was your issue,
and you could catch it,

40:51.715 --> 40:53.630
would you try to catch it?

40:53.630 --> 40:55.196
Yes.

40:55.196 --> 40:58.939
Then when you caught it,
what would you do with it?

40:58.939 --> 41:00.288
Let me guess.

41:00.288 --> 41:03.901
You're asking us to find
and kill this rabbit?

41:03.901 --> 41:05.293
Is that what you think?

41:06.730 --> 41:09.820
You think a simple rabbit
hunt will solve your problems?

41:10.864 --> 41:12.562
There's no stakes there.

41:12.562 --> 41:14.346
I don't think that'll do anything.

41:15.608 --> 41:17.523
Then what's the game?

41:17.523 --> 41:18.611
"The game?"

41:18.611 --> 41:19.525
There's no game.

41:20.787 --> 41:21.614
This is life.

41:22.833 --> 41:23.877
This is survival.

41:27.315 --> 41:28.447
How are y'all feeling?

41:32.669 --> 41:35.062
Those pills you just
took weren't vitamins.

41:35.062 --> 41:37.021
They're a fast acting poison.

41:37.021 --> 41:39.066
You'll all be dead within 20 minutes.

41:39.066 --> 41:40.067
You're jokin' with us!

41:41.199 --> 41:42.548
What the fuck?!

41:42.548 --> 41:45.508
I assure you, your death is imminent,

41:45.508 --> 41:48.249
unless-
- What do we need to do?!

41:48.249 --> 41:50.774
You can use these trackers
and find the rabbit.

41:50.774 --> 41:53.254
The rabbit has the antidote in
its blood.

41:54.168 --> 41:54.995
Catch it,

41:55.953 --> 41:57.041
and you live.

43:24.998 --> 43:26.957
- Move!

44:14.787 --> 44:16.397
Instead of anger,

44:16.397 --> 44:18.399
let's focus on relief.

44:18.399 --> 44:21.141
The fear of death changes most.

44:22.360 --> 44:25.102
How will it change you?

44:36.200 --> 44:38.289
I wanna get the fuck out of here.

44:38.289 --> 44:40.117
Likewise.

44:40.117 --> 44:41.292
And why is that?

44:43.686 --> 44:45.688
Tobin tried to kill us out there.

44:45.688 --> 44:46.819
What?

44:46.819 --> 44:47.777
How?

44:47.777 --> 44:49.604
He fucking poisoned us.

44:49.604 --> 44:50.518
Focus!

44:50.518 --> 44:52.695
I'll ask a simple question.

44:54.087 --> 44:55.088
Do you want to stay?

44:56.394 --> 44:57.569
Fuck no.

44:57.569 --> 44:59.919
I want to.

44:59.919 --> 45:02.530
Lily, do you want to stay?

45:03.793 --> 45:06.360
I'd like to keep going
and see where we're headed.

45:06.360 --> 45:07.405
Jesse?

45:08.580 --> 45:10.713
Not 100% sure.

45:10.713 --> 45:11.714
Yes or no!

45:13.498 --> 45:15.848
If you'd let me finish,

45:15.848 --> 45:19.765
I was going to say, I'm not 100%
sure...

45:19.765 --> 45:22.072
But, yes.

45:25.379 --> 45:28.469
After you got poisoned today?

45:28.469 --> 45:30.123
